> This Thai-inspired pork stir-fry is our take on a classic Pad Krapow Moo. The tender
> green beans add some welcome vibrancy while the chilli and ginger provide a bit of bite.

Trim and halve the @green beans{150%g}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and
grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Use a teaspoon to easily scrape away the
peel.

Zest, then cut @lime{1} into thick wedges. Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Halve the @chilli{1}(halved, core and seeds removed) lengthways then discard the core
and seeds. Finely chop.

Pour @water{300%ml}(cold salted) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting lid.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pot{} from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, place a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.
Season the @pork loin steak{300%g} with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once the oil is hot, fry the pork until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Reduce heat to medium and fry for ~{4-6%minutes}, turning every ~{2%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from the pan. Cover to keep warm and allow to rest.

> IMPORTANT: Pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

When hot, add the green beans.

Fry until just cooked through but still crisp, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the onion, garlic, ginger and chilli (use less if you don't like spice) to the pan
along with @sugar{1%tsp}.

> Double sugar for 4p.

Cook until fragrant, stirring often, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in lime zest, @soy sauce{1%sachet} and @water{25%ml}.

> Double water for 4p.

Cook for ~{1%minute}, stirring often.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice and pork between plates.

Serve with the stir-fried veg, drizzling over any sauce remaining in the pan.

Garnish with a sprinkling of chopped coriander.

Serve lime wedges alongside.